Crispy Labneh Chicken & Tzatziki...well, tzatziki adjacent! I am using labneh to marinate the chicken thighs to get the juiciest ever bird! As always, using Yaza Labneh because it is creamier than store bought tzatziki or labneh!

Ingredients:
6 chicken thighs.
1/2 cup labneh.
1 garlic clove.
1 lemon (zest and juice of 1/2)
3 eggs.
2 tbsp milk.
3 cups panko.
1/4 flour.
1 tsp kosher salt.
1 tsp onion powder.
1/2 tsp white pepper.
1 tsp garlic powder.
Olive oil for frying.

Tzatziki (ish):
1/2 cup labneh (Yaza).
1/3 english cucumber (grated and moisture squeezed out).
1 tiny garlic clove or 1/2 medium one.
1 lemon (zest of 1 and only a squeeze of juice).
1 serrano (seeded and finely chopped).
2 tbsp chives.
3 tbsp fresh dill.
1 tbsp olive oil.

Directions:
Pound the chicken thighs until fairly thin.
Cover the chicken in the labneh, lemon zest, lemon juice, garlic and salt. Marinate for 24 hrs or overnight.
Whisk the egg with milk and strain onto a plate.
 Mix the flour with salt, white pepper, garlic and onion powder.
Coat the chicken well on both sides with the flour, dredge with the egg and coat with the panko. Back to the egg wash and panko again. Let it sit for 15-25 min on a wire rack.
Mix the labneh, cucumber, herbs, lemon zest, juice (adjust to taste), salt and olive oil.
Preheat a pan on medium high for 2-3 min. Add plenty of olive oil and lower to medium high.
Fry the chicken on medium high until golden on both sides, about 2-3 min per side. Remove from the pan and hit them with flaky salt.
Top the chicken with the sauce and fresh herbs, serve with lemon.

I’m in my pistachio era and my latest is pistachio labneh made @Yaza.foods labneh. It only has 2 ingredients: cultured milk and salt - no milk powders, no thickeners. #sponsored I use it all the time for sandwiches, dips and dressings. When I want to jazz it up, I blend it with different mediterranean ingredients like pistachios, mint, dill and lemon for the herby green labneh. It’s a high-protein fun dip for summer and packed with probiotics for your gut health! 🙌
INGREDIENTS
1 (12-ounce) tub @Yaza.foods labneh
1 cup pistachios
2 tablespoons extra virgin olive oil
¼ cup fresh dill
¼ cup fresh mint leaves
½ lemon, zest and juice

VIRAL BROWN BUTTER DATES 

Looking for a super quick, guilt free dessert that comes together in minutes? Here’s your answer to that! 

I’ve seen butter seared dates go viral recently and I had to see if they went viral for good reason. I can confidently confirm that it’s for good reason. Dates on their own are cloyingly sweet so I had to figure out a healthy way to balance that sweetness. 

I had to go Middle Eastern of course, so I chose pomegranate molasses to balance the sweetness, pistachios for a little saltiness and crunch, labne and honey mixed together as the base of the dish and then of course the brown butter seared dates along with the butter and olive oil I seared them in. Garnished the dish with a pinch of sumac for a little more sourness and flakey salt for some much needed salinity in the dish! 

Whether you’re looking for a guilt free dessert or a decadent post workout snack……

YOU GOTTA TRY THIS ONE OUT!
